name: analytics
title: Google Analytics API
description: View and manage your Google Analytics data

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters. Overrides userIp if both are provided.

userIp.description: IP address of the site where the request originates. Use this if you want to enforce per-user limits.

childLink.description: Child link for an account entry. Points to the list of web properties for this account.

href.description: Link to the list of web properties for this account.

type.description: Type of the child link. Its value is "analytics#webproperties".

updated.description: Time the account was last modified.

itemsPerPage.description: The maximum number of entries the response can contain, regardless of the actual number of entries returned. Its value ranges from 1 to 10,000 with a value of 1000 by default, or otherwise specified by the max-results query parameter.

nextLink.description: Next link for this account collection.

previousLink.description: Previous link for this account collection.

startIndex.description: The starting index of the entries, which is 1 by default or otherwise specified by the start-index query parameter.

totalResults.description: The total number of results for the query, regardless of the number of results in the response.

username.description: Email ID of the authenticated user

columnHeaders.description: Column headers that list dimension names followed by the metric names. The order of dimensions and metrics is same as specified in the request.

columnType.description: Column Type. Either DIMENSION or METRIC.

dataType.description: Data type. Dimension column headers have only STRING as the data type. Metric column headers have data types for metric values such as INTEGER, DOUBLE, CURRENCY etc.

containsSampledData.description: Determines if Analytics data contains samples.

id.description: Unique ID for this data response.

itemsPerPage.description: The maximum number of rows the response can contain, regardless of the actual number of rows returned. Its value ranges from 1 to 10,000 with a value of 1000 by default, or otherwise specified by the max-results query parameter.

nextLink.description: Link to next page for this Analytics data query.

previousLink.description: Link to previous page for this Analytics data query.

profileInfo.description: Information for the profile, for which the Analytics data was requested.

accountId.description: Account ID to which this profile belongs.

internalWebPropertyId.description: Internal ID for the web property to which this profile belongs.

webPropertyId.description: Web Property ID to which this profile belongs.

filters.description: Comma-separated list of dimension or metric filters.

sort.description: List of dimensions or metrics based on which Analytics data is sorted.

rows.description: Analytics data rows, where each row contains a list of dimension values followed by the metric values. The order of dimensions and metrics is same as specified in the request.

totalResults.description: The total number of rows for the query, regardless of the number of rows in the response.

totalsForAllResults.description: Total values for the requested metrics over all the results, not just the results returned in this response. The order of the metric totals is same as the metric order specified in the request.

additionalProperties.description: Key-value pair for the total value of a metric. Key is the metric name and the value is the total value for that metric.

accountId.description: Account ID to which this goal belongs.

active.description: Determines whether this goal is active.

eventDetails.description: Details for the goal of the type EVENT.

comparisonType.description: Type of comparison. Possible values are LESS_THAN, GREATER_THAN or EQUAL.

matchType.description: Type of the match to be performed. Possible values are REGEXP, BEGINS_WITH, or EXACT.

type.description: Type of this event condition. Possible values are CATEGORY, ACTION, LABEL, or VALUE.

useEventValue.description: Determines if the event value should be used as the value for this goal.

internalWebPropertyId.description: Internal ID for the web property to which this goal belongs.

kind.description: Resource type for an Analytics goal.

parentLink.description: Parent link for a goal. Points to the profile to which this goal belongs.

href.description: Link to the profile to which this goal belongs.

profileId.description: Profile ID to which this goal belongs.

type.description: Goal type. Possible values are URL_DESTINATION, VISIT_TIME_ON_SITE, VISIT_NUM_PAGES, AND EVENT.

updated.description: Time this goal was last modified.

urlDestinationDetails.description: Details for the goal of the type URL_DESTINATION.

caseSensitive.description: Determines if the goal URL must exactly match the capitalization of visited URLs.

firstStepRequired.description: Determines if the first step in this goal is required.

matchType.description: Match type for the goal URL. Possible values are HEAD, EXACT, or REGEX.

steps.description: List of steps configured for this goal funnel.

visitNumPagesDetails.description: Details for the goal of the type VISIT_NUM_PAGES.

comparisonType.description: Type of comparison. Possible values are LESS_THAN, GREATER_THAN, or EQUAL.

visitTimeOnSiteDetails.description: Details for the goal of the type VISIT_TIME_ON_SITE.

comparisonType.description: Type of comparison. Possible values are LESS_THAN or GREATER_THAN.

webPropertyId.description: Web property ID to which this goal belongs. The web property ID is of the form UA-XXXXX-YY.

itemsPerPage.description: The maximum number of resources the response can contain, regardless of the actual number of resources returned. Its value ranges from 1 to 10,000 with a value of 1000 by default, or otherwise specified by the max-results query parameter.

nextLink.description: Link to next page for this goal collection.

previousLink.description: Link to previous page for this goal collection.

startIndex.description: The starting index of the resources, which is 1 by default or otherwise specified by the start-index query parameter.

totalResults.description: The total number of results for the query, regardless of the number of resources in the result.

username.description: Email ID of the authenticated user

accountId.description: Account ID to which this profile belongs.

childLink.description: Child link for this profile. Points to the list of goals for this profile.

href.description: Link to the list of goals for this profile.

currency.description: The currency type associated with this profile.

excludeQueryParameters.description: The query parameters that are excluded from this profile.

internalWebPropertyId.description: Internal ID for the web property to which this profile belongs.

parentLink.description: Parent link for this profile. Points to the web property to which this profile belongs.

href.description: Link to the web property to which this profile belongs.

siteSearchCategoryParameters.description: Site search category parameters for this profile.

siteSearchQueryParameters.description: The site search query parameters for this profile.

timezone.description: Time zone for which this profile has been configured.

updated.description: Time this profile was last modified.

webPropertyId.description: Web property ID of the form UA-XXXXX-YY to which this profile belongs.

previousLink.description: Link to previous page for this profile collection.

kind.description: Resource type for Analytics advanced segment.

segmentId.description: Segment ID. Can be used with the 'segment' parameter in Data Feed.

updated.description: Time the advanced segment was last modified.

previousLink.description: Link to previous page for this web property collection.

accountId.description: Account ID to which this web property belongs.

childLink.description: Child link for this web property. Points to the list of profiles for this web property.

href.description: Link to the list of profiles for this web property.

type.description: Type of the parent link. Its value is "analytics#profiles".

created.description: Time this web property was created.

id.description: Web property ID of the form UA-XXXXX-YY.

internalWebPropertyId.description: Internal ID for this web property.

parentLink.description: Parent link for this web property. Points to the account to which this web property belongs.

websiteUrl.description: Website url for this web property.

get.description: Returns Analytics data for a profile.

dimensions.description: A comma-separated list of Analytics dimensions. E.g., 'ga:browser,ga:city'.

end-date.description: End date for fetching Analytics data. All requests should specify an end date formatted as YYYY-MM-DD.

filters.description: A comma-separated list of dimension or metric filters to be applied to Analytics data.

ids.description: Unique table ID for retrieving Analytics data. Table ID is of the form ga:XXXX, where XXXX is the Analytics profile ID.

max-results.description: The maximum number of entries to include in this feed.

metrics.description: A comma-separated list of Analytics metrics. E.g., 'ga:visits,ga:pageviews'. At least one metric must be specified.

segment.description: An Analytics advanced segment to be applied to data.

sort.description: A comma-separated list of dimensions or metrics that determine the sort order for Analytics data.

start-date.description: Start date for fetching Analytics data. All requests should specify a start date formatted as YYYY-MM-DD.

start-index.description: An index of the first entity to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.

list.description: Lists all accounts to which the user has access.

max-results.description: The maximum number of accounts to include in this response.

start-index.description: An index of the first account to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.

list.description: Lists goals to which the user has access.

accountId.description: Account ID to retrieve goals for. Can either be a specific account ID or '~all', which refers to all the accounts that user has access to.

max-results.description: The maximum number of goals to include in this response.

profileId.description: Profile ID to retrieve goals for. Can either be a specific profile ID or '~all', which refers to all the profiles that user has access to.

start-index.description: An index of the first goal to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.

webPropertyId.description: Web property ID to retrieve goals for. Can either be a specific web property ID or '~all', which refers to all the web properties that user has access to.

list.description: Lists profiles to which the user has access.

accountId.description: Account ID for the profiles to retrieve. Can either be a specific account ID or '~all', which refers to all the accounts to which the user has access.

max-results.description: The maximum number of profiles to include in this response.

start-index.description: An index of the first entity to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.

webPropertyId.description: Web property ID for the profiles to retrieve. Can either be a specific web property ID or '~all', which refers to all the web properties to which the user has access.

list.description: Lists advanced segments to which the user has access.

max-results.description: The maximum number of advanced segments to include in this response.

start-index.description: An index of the first advanced segment to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.

accountId.description: Account ID to retrieve web properties for. Can either be a specific account ID or '~all', which refers to all the accounts that user has access to.

max-results.description: The maximum number of web properties to include in this response.

start-index.description: An index of the first entity to retrieve. Use this parameter as a pagination mechanism along with the max-results parameter.
